ights%20To%20Meet%20Adoption%20Demand%2C%20Probe%20Finds%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%3ESouth%20Korea's%20government%20enabled%20the%20%26quot%3Bmass%20exportation%26quot%3B%20of%20children%20with%20private%20adoption%20agencies%20by%20fabricating%20birth%20records%20and%20failing%20to%20follow%20consent%20procedures%2C%20a%20long-awaited%20investigation%20has%20found.%20According%20to%20%3Cem%3ECNN%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20%C2%A0the%20country%2C%20which%20remains%20one%20of%20the%20biggest%20exporters%20of%20babies%20in%20the%20world%2C%20has%20sent%20over%20200%2C000%20South%20Korean%20children%20overseas%20since%20the%201950s%2C%20when%20the%20impoverished%20country%20was%20rebuilding%20from%20the%20devastation%20of%20World%20War%20II%20and%20the%20Korean%20War.%20Many%20of%20those%20adopted%20children%2C%20now%20adults%20trying%20to%20trace%20their%20origins%2C%20accused%20agencies%20of%20coercion%20and%20deception%2C%20including%20in%20some%20cases%20forcibly%20removing%20them%20from%20their%20mothers.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ENow%2C%20after%20a%20three-year%20investigation%2C%20the%20government's%20Truth%20and%20Reconciliation%20Commission%20released%20its%20findings%20on%20the%20first%20100%20cases%20out%20of%20367%20total%20petitions%20filed%20by%20adoptees%20sent%20overseas%20between%201964%20and%201999%2C%20per%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noindex%2Cnofollow%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fedition.cnn.com%2F2025%2F03%2F26%2Fasia%2Fsouth-korea-overseas-adoption-investigation-intl-hnk%2Findex.html%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3ECNN%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E.%20It%20found%20that%2056%20of%20the%20100%20were%20%26quot%3Bvictims%26quot%3B%20of%20the%20government's%20negligence%2C%20which%20amounted%20to%20a%20violation%20of%20their%20rights%20under%20the%20Korean%20constitution%20and%20international%20convention.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20the%20investigation%2C%20local%20agencies%20collaborated%20with%20foreign%20groups%20to%20mass%20export%20South%20Korean%20children%2C%20driven%20by%20monthly%20quotas%20set%20by%20overseas%20demand.%20Many%20adoptions%20occurred%20through%20dubious%20or%20outright%20unethical%20means%2C%20it%20said.%20The%20commission%20found%20evidence%20of%20fabricated%20records%2C%20including%20%26quot%3Bdeliberate%20identity%20substitution%26quot%3B%20and%20false%20reports%20that%20the%20children%20being%20adopted%20had%20been%20abandoned%20by%20their%20birth%20parents.%20It%20said%20that%20there%20was%20a%20lack%20of%20proper%20parental%20consent%20for%20adoption%20as%20well.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20commission%20noted%20that%20such%20lack%20of%20oversight%20led%20to%20large-scale%20inter-country%20adoptions%2C%20with%20many%20children%20losing%20their%20true%20identities%20and%20family%20histories%20due%20to%20falsified%20or%20fabricated%20records.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EAlso%20read%20%7C%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fworld-news%2Fjack-dorseys-fintech-firm-block-cuts-over-900-jobs-want-to-give-you-straight-facts-8024165%5C%22%3EJack%20Dorsey's%20Fintech%20Firm%20Block%20Cuts%20Over%20900%20Jobs%3A%20%26quot%3BWant%20To%20Give%20You%20Straight%20Facts%26quot%3B%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20commission%20determined%20%26quot%3Bthe%20state%20violated%20the%20human%20rights%20of%20adoptees%20protected%20under%20the%20constitution%20and%20international%20agreements%20by%20neglecting%20its%20duty%20to%20ensure%20basic%20human%20rights%2C%20including%20inadequate%20legislation%2C%20poor%20management%20and%20oversight%2C%20and%20failures%20in%20implementing%20proper%20administrative%20procedures%20while%20sending%20large%20numbers%20of%20children%20abroad%2C%26quot%3B%20as%20per%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.independent.co.uk%2Fasia%2Feast-asia%2Fsouth-korea-adoption-fraud-children-human-rights-b2722464.html%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3EThe%20Independent%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BNumerous%20legal%20and%20policy%20shortcomings%20emerged%2C%26quot%3B%20commission%20head%20Park%20Sun%20Young%20said%2C%20adding%2C%20%26quot%3BThese%20violations%20should%20never%20have%20occurred.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20investigation%20of%20more%20than%20300%20cases%20began%20in%202022%20and%20is%20due%20to%20end%20in%20May.%20Till%20then%2C%20the%20commission%20has%20recommended%20that%20the%20government%20offer%20an%20official%20apology%2C%20conduct%20a%20comprehensive%20survey%20of%20adoptees'%20citizenship%20status%20and%20come%20up%20with%20remedies%20for%20victims%20whose%20identities%20were%20falsified.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1743081600000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2025-03%2F9eb70io8_adoption-generic_625x300_27_March_25.jpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fworld-news%2Fsouth-korea-worlds-largest-baby-exporter-violated-human-rights-to-meet-adoption-demand-probe-finds-8024729%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22South%20Korea's%20government%20enabled%20the%20%26quot%3Bmass%20exportation%26quot%3B%20of%20children%20with%20private%20adoption%20agencies%20by%20fabricating%20birth%20records%20and%20failing%20to%20follow%20consent%20procedures%2C%20a%20long-awaited%20investigation%20has%20found.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Prithviraj%20on%20Telugu%20remake%20of%20L2%3A%20Empuraan%20with%20Salman-Chiranjeevi%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1743081593000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fstatic.toiimg.com%2Fphoto%2Fmsid-119599507%2Cimgsize-44024.cms%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fentertainment%2Fhindi%2Fbollywood%2Fnews%2Fprithviraj-sukumaran-hints-at-telugu-remake-of-l2-empuraan-with-salman-khan-and-chiranjeevi-i-know-for-a-fact-that-%2Farticleshow%2F119599507.cms%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20border%3D%5C%220%5C%22%20align%3D%5C%22left%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofin