5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Etax%20return%3C%2Fa%3E.%20This%20mistake%20didn't%20get%20me%20audited%20or%20raise%20red%20flags%20from%20my%20accountant.%20I%20made%20this%20mistake%20before%20the%202024%20tax%20year%20even%20started%2C%20way%20back%20in%20December%202023%2C%20during%20health%20insurance%20open%20enrollment.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMy%20biggest%20tax%20mistake%20of%202024%20was%20failing%20to%20sign%20up%20for%20a%20health%20insurance%20plan%20that%20was%20eligible%20for%20a%20health%20savings%20account.%20Because%20of%20this%20mistake%2C%20I%20wasn't%20allowed%20to%20use%20one%20of%20the%20most%20sought-after%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Ftaxes%2Fwhat-can-i-deduct-on-my-taxes%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Etax%20deductions%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20here's%20the%20kicker%3A%20After%20seeing%20how%20this%20situation%20played%20out%20for%20my%202024%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Ftaxes%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Etaxes%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20I'm%20deliberately%20making%20the%20same%20%26quot%3Bmistake%26quot%3B%20again%20in%202025.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%226f853dda-47b5-4847-add1-1c107ec96056%5C%22%3EHSAs%20are%20often%20the%20best%20choice%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EOpen%20enrollment%20is%20the%20special%20time%20of%20year%20when%20people%20can%20choose%20new%20health%20insurance%20plans.%20If%20you%20qualify%2C%20it's%20a%20great%20idea%20to%20choose%20a%20health%20insurance%20plan%20that%20is%20eligible%20for%20an%20HSA.%20Having%20an%20HSA%20is%20a%20sweet%20tax%20perk%2C%20because%20it%20gives%20you%20another%20option%20to%20sock%20away%20thousands%20of%20dollars%20of%20tax-deductible%20money.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%202024%20tax%20purposes%2C%20people%20with%20HSAs%20were%20allowed%20to%20contribute%20up%20to%20%244%2C150%20(for%20self-only%20coverage)%20or%20%248%2C300%20(for%20family%20coverage)%20of%20tax-deductible%20money%20to%20these%20special%20savings%20accounts.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnd%20HSAs%20give%20you%20flexible%20options%20for%20how%20to%20use%20the%20money%20%E2%80%94%20these%20accounts%20are%20not%20%26quot%3Buse%20it%20or%20lose%20it.%26quot%3B%20You%20can%20use%20your%20HSA%20cash%20to%20pay%20for%20a%20wide%20range%20of%20healthcare%20costs%20at%20any%20time.%20Or%20you%20can%20invest%20your%20HSA%20dollars%20for%20the%20longer%20term%20and%20use%20the%20account%20for%20your%20future%20healthcare%20costs%2C%20or%20as%20an%20additional%20source%20of%20retirement%20savings.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22ecf94071-d4f9-4ec0-bf51-18958bcaa927%5C%22%3EHow%20my%20big%20tax%20mistake%20happened%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20there's%20a%20catch.%20In%20exchange%20for%20that%20sweet%20HSA%20tax%20break%2C%20the%20IRS%20expects%20HSA%20owners%20to%20have%20some%20skin%20in%20the%20game%20and%20pay%20for%20more%20of%20their%20own%20healthcare%20costs.%20HSA-eligible%20plans%20must%20be%20high-deductible%20health%20plans.%20For%202024%2C%20HDHPs%20were%20required%20to%20have%20minimum%20annual%20deductibles%20of%20%241%2C600%20for%20self-only%20coverage%20and%20%243%2C200%20for%20family%20coverage.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWay%20back%20in%20December%202023%2C%20when%20I%20was%20signing%20up%20for%20new%20health%20insurance%20for%202024%2C%20I%20thought%20I%20was%20signing%20up%20for%20an%20HSA-eligible%20plan.%20But%20I%20was%20wrong.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHere's%20what%20happened.%20I'm%20self-employed%2C%20and%20my%20family%20gets%20health%20insurance%20through%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.healthcare.gov%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EHealthCare.gov%3C%2Fa%3E%20marketplace.%20During%20open%20enrollment%2C%20I%20was%20scrolling%20through%20the%20list%20of%20health%20insurance%20plans%20on%20HealthCare.gov%20that%20were%20available%20for%20my%20family%20to%20choose%2C%20and%20I%20clicked%20on%20one%20that%20I%20thought%20was%20HSA-eligible.%20It%20had%20a%20high%20deductible%20(more%20than%20%243%2C200%20for%202024)%20and%20high%20out-of-pocket%20costs.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20I%20misunderstood%20some%20numbers%20and%20details%20in%20the%20fine%20print.%20The%20plan%20that%20I%20thought%20was%20HSA-eligible%20(because%20it%20had%20a%20high%20deductible%20and%20high%20out-of-pocket%20costs)%20actually%20was%20not%20eligible%20%E2%80%94%20because%20the%20plan's%20out-of-pocket%20costs%20were%20too%20high%20to%20qualify.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHSA-eligible%20plans%20for%202024%20had%20maximum%20out-of-pocket%20costs%20(including%20the%20deductible)%20of%20%248%2C050%20for%20self-only%20coverage%2C%20or%20%2416%2C100%20for%20family%20coverage.%20The%20plan%20I%20chose%20had%20maximum%20out-of-pocket%20costs%20of%20over%20%2418%2C000%20%E2%80%94%20not%20HSA-eligible.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%228a18f8c0-2d49-4286-863e-1646af81afaf%5C%22%3EHow%20much%20my%202024%20tax%20mistake%20cost%20me%20%E2%80%94%20and%20why%20I%20did%20it%20again%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EBecause%20I%20accidentally%20chose%20the%20wrong%20health%20insurance%20plan%2C%20my%20family%20went%20through%202024%20without%20being%20able%20to%20save%20tax-deductible%20money%20for%20healthcare%20expenses.%20I%20missed%20out%20on%20up%20to%20%248%2C300%20of%20tax%20deductions%20that%20could%20have%20gone%20on%20my%202024%20tax%20return.%20If%20you're%20in%20the%2022%25%20tax%20bracket%2C%20%248%2C300%20of%20tax%20deductions%20equals%20about%20%241%2C826%20of%20tax%20savings.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20here's%20what%20I%20learned%20from%20my%202024%20tax%20mistake%3A%20I%20liked%20our%20non-HSA%20health%20insurance%20better%20than%20the%20other%20choices.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOur%20health%20insurance%20plan%20didn't%20give%20us%20HSA%20tax%20breaks%2C%20but%20it%20gave%20us%20a%20lower%2C%20affordable%20monthly%20premium.%20It%20allowed%20us%20to%20keep%20our%20favorite%20doctors%20and%20clinics%20in-network.%20Our%20health%20insurance%20company%20is%20easy%20to%20work%20with%2C%20and%20we%20understand%20which%20preventative%20care%20and%20screenings%20are%20covered.%20This%20plan%20is%20the%20best%20deal%20we%20can%20find.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20all%20of%20these%20reasons%2C%20I%20kept%20the%20same%20health%20insurance%20plan%20for%202025.%20This%20time%2C%20it%20wasn't%20a%20mistake%2C%20it%20was%20a%20choice.%20I%20knew%20going%20in%20that%20it%20wouldn't%20have%20an%20HSA.%20And%20our%202025%20health%20insurance%20premium%20is%20%2480%20lower%20a%20month!%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWeighing%20the%20options%20for%20health%20insurance%20is%20never%20easy%2C%20but%20if%20you%20make%20the%20same%20tax%20mistake%20that%20I%20did%2C%20don't%20beat%20yourself%20up%20about%20it.%20Peace%20of%20mind%20and%20consistency%20can%20be%20worth%20more%20than%20a%20tax%20break.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Caside%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EWorried%20about%20your%20finances%3F%20Consider%20a%20financial%20advisor.%C2%A0%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fsmartasset.com%2Fretirement%2Ffind-a-financial-planner%3Futm_source%3Dbusinessinsider%26utm_medium%3Dcpc%26utm_campaign%3Dbus__falc_bicontent%26utm_content%3DBI%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3EFinding%20a%20financial%20advisor%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20doesn't%20have%20to%20be%20hard.%20SmartAsset's%20free%20tool%20matches%20you%20with%20up%20to%20three%20fiduciary%20financial%20advisors%20who%20serve%20your%20area%20in%20minutes.%20Each%20advisor%20has%20been%20vetted%20by%20SmartAsset%20and%20is%20held%20to%20a%20fiduciary%20standard%20to%20act%20in%20your%20best%20interests.%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fsmartasset.com%2Fretirement%2Ffind-a-financial-planner%3Futm_source%3Dbusinessinsider%26utm_medium%3Dcpc%26utm_campaign%3Dbus__falc_bicontent%26utm_content%3DBI%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3E%20Start%20your%20search%20now.%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3C%2Faside%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmade-mistake-taxes