0people%20with%20Armenian%20heritage%20rose%20in%20our%20city%2C%20and%20we%20needed%20to%20flee%20to%20Moscow.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWe%20then%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Frefugees-journey-how-a-fraction-of-refugees-come-to-us-2022-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eapplied%20for%20refugee%20status%20in%20the%20US%3C%2Fa%3E.%20It%20was%20a%20long%20process%20that%20involved%20health%20screenings%2C%20psychological%20evaluations%2C%20and%20verifying%20my%20parents'%20education.%20After%20years%2C%20we%20were%20finally%20approved%20to%20move%20to%20the%20US%20when%20I%20was%2011.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20a%20refugee%2C%20when%20you%20think%20of%20the%20US%2C%20you%20always%20dream%20of%20living%20in%20New%20York%20City%2C%20Florida%2C%20or%20California.%20We%20landed%20in%20Jacksonville%2C%20Florida%2C%20and%20I%20was%20thrilled.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWithin%20two%20weeks%2C%20I%20used%20my%20life%20savings%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftaking-grandchild-to-disney-world-first-time-discoveries-2025-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ego%20to%20Disney%20World%3C%2Fa%3E.%20It%20was%20truly%20a%20dream%20come%20true.%20So%20were%20the%20more%20mundane%20aspects%20of%20my%20new%20life.%20I%20had%20experienced%20sharing%20a%20bathroom%20with%20four%20other%20families%20and%20being%20food%20insecure.%20I%20could%20literally%20and%20figuratively%20have%20all%20the%20bananas%20I%20wanted%20in%20the%20US.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22b129102d-e52c-4b39-b180-19b558afdde8%5C%22%3EI%20started%20a%20career%20in%20wealth%20management%2C%20but%20it%20wasn't%20for%20me%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20I%20arrived%20in%20the%20US%2C%20I%20could%20say%2C%20%26quot%3BMy%20name%20is%20Orhan%2C%26quot%3B%20and%20that%20was%20about%20it.%20I%20started%20fifth%20grade%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fguides%2Flearning%2Fhow-to-learn-english-esl%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Elearned%20English%3C%2Fa%3E%20alongside%20my%20parents.%20I%20was%20so%20happy%20to%20be%20in%20Florida%2C%20but%20I%20could%20see%20how%20challenging%20it%20was%20for%20them.%20My%20mother%20has%20multiple%20master's%20degrees%20in%20art%2C%20and%20my%20dad%20was%20an%20engineer%20with%20his%20own%20lab%20in%20Azerbaijan.%20In%20the%20US%2C%20they%20had%20to%20start%20over%2C%20beginning%20by%20learning%20the%20language.%20Their%20advanced%20education%20didn't%20mean%20much%20here.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWe%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Freasons-happy-philadelphia-after-los-angeles-2023-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Emoved%20to%20Philadelphia%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20so%20my%20dad%20could%20attend%20technical%20school.%20I%20went%20to%20an%20inner-city%20high%20school%20in%20Philadelphia%2C%20which%20forced%20me%20to%20develop%20a%20thick%20skin.%20After%20graduation%2C%20I%20was%20accepted%20to%20Penn%20State%20and%20later%20got%20an%20internship%20with%20Morgan%20Stanley.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20graduated%20with%20multiple%20job%20offers%20in%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhabits-millionaire-clients-have-in-common-financial-planner-2024-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ewealth%20managemen%3C%2Fa%3Et.%20I%20was%20only%2022%2C%20but%20I%20had%20my%20own%20office%20and%20a%20lucrative%20career%20ahead%20of%20me.%20But%20I%20knew%20that%20wasn't%20my%20path.%20I%20couldn't%20see%20myself%20doing%20the%20office%20grind%20for%20decades.%20More%20importantly%2C%20I%20felt%20a%20disconnect%20with%20my%20wealthy%20clients.%20If%20I%20was%20going%20to%20spend%20my%20life%20doing%20something%2C%20I%20wanted%20it%20to%20be%20very%20straightforward%2C%20transparent%2C%20and%20honest.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22da8ecf8d-e9d9-4d25-9a73-8f903b44d359%5C%22%3EI%20run%20a%20multimillion-dollar%20business%2C%20but%20drive%20a%20used%20car%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EI%20spoke%20with%20my%20dad%2C%20and%20we%20began%20researching%20franchise%20opportunities.%20Everyone%20else%20thought%20I%20was%20nuts%2C%20stepping%20away%20from%20my%20finance%20career%2C%20but%20my%20parents%20believed%20in%20me%20so%20much%20that%20they%20took%20out%20a%20second%20mortgage%20to%20help%20me%20afford%20my%20first%20restaurant.%20To%20this%20day%2C%20my%20dad%20and%20I%20are%2050-50%20partners.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221355%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Orhan%20Veli%20%20with%20his%20dad%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F67dd9f0263d72727e197edab%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22967%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EOrhan%20Veli%20and%20his%20dad%20are%20still%20business%20partners.%3Cp%3ECourtesy%20of%20Orhan%20Veli%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EThose%20early%20years%20were%20rough.%20I%20was%2023%20and%20doing%20nothing%20but%20working%2C%20earning%20about%20%244%20an%20hour.%20After%20the%20financial%20crisis%20in%202008%2C%20I%20learned%20how%20to%20operate%20a%20business%20with%20very%20slim%20margins%2C%20which%20ultimately%20made%20me%20a%20better%20businessman.%20Today%2C%20I%20own%2011%20SaladWorks%20locations%3B%20my%20restaurants%20brought%20in%20nearly%20%2412%20million%20in%202024.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20have%20some%20financial%20independence%2C%20and%20I%20don't%20need%20to%20worry%20about%20money%20the%20way%20I%20used%20to.%20Still%2C%20I%20live%20modestly.%20My%20three%20kids%20are%20in%20public%20school%2C%20and%20my%20wife%20and%20I%20own%20an%20average%20home%20in%20our%20town.%20We%20both%20drive%20used%20cars%20%E2%80%94%20a%20Volkswagen%20for%20me%20and%20a%20Lexus%20for%20her.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22a456641a-d01d-4e86-8675-29dff9ec2169%5C%22%3EI've%20used%20my%20financial%20security%20to%20help%20other%20refugees%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EMy%20wife%2C%20Anastasiya%2C%20is%20Ukrainian.%20When%20the%20war%20broke%20out%2C%20we%20both%20wanted%20to%20help%20people.%20I%20knew%20what%20it%20was%20like%20to%20have%20to%20flee%20your