0href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Floved-seattle-had-to-leave-now-live-suburbs-happier-housing-2024-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ESeattle%3C%2Fa%3E%20so%20he%20could%20design%20Microsoft's%20line%20of%20phones%20and%20tablets.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20job%20came%20with%20an%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fquadrupled-salary-big-tech-job-hopping-negotiating-2024-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eeye-watering%20salary%20bump%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20a%20bonus%2C%20and%20stock%20options%20we%20had%20seen%20only%20in%20the%20movies.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBoth%20of%20us%20had%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmoved-chicago-from-portland-big-city-life-affordable-2024-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Emoved%20to%20Chicago%3C%2Fa%3E%20soon%20after%20graduating%20from%20college.%20We%20loved%20the%20city%20and%20didn't%20want%20to%20leave%2C%20but%20we%20questioned%20whether%20an%20offer%20like%20this%20would%20ever%20come%20again.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3E%26quot%3B%3C%2Fem%3EWe'll%20move%20back%20if%20we%20hate%20it%2C%26quot%3B%20we%20promised%20ourselves.%20We%20spent%20the%20next%2012%20years%20breaking%20that%20promise.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22b2fe5c38-753b-4824-bb04-05055a8c166c%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EAdapting%20to%20life%20in%20Seattle%20was%20rough%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EWe%20found%20early%20on%20that%20people%20seemed%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fincredibly-lonely-high-paying-tech-job-seattle-2023-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ekeep%20to%20themselves%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20weren't%20looking%20for%20new%20friends.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EStill%2C%20there%20were%20some%20bright%20spots%20as%20the%20years%20ticked%20by.%20We%20had%20financial%20security%20for%20the%20first%20time%20in%20our%20lives%2C%20a%20few%20friends%20(all%20transplants%20like%20us)%2C%20and%20a%20Craftsman%20house%20we%20spent%20weekends%20remodeling.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2248be97ff-f8fb-4056-b9c6-0ac437b59bb8%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3ELife%20was%20good%20on%20paper%2C%20but%20behind%20closed%20doors%20we%20were%20struggling%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EI%20got%20pregnant%20three%20months%20after%20moving%20and%20lost%20the%20baby%20at%2020%20weeks.%20Three%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fguides%2Fhealth%2Freproductive-health%2Fmiscarriage-rates-by-week%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Emiscarriages%3C%2Fa%3E%20followed%2C%20along%20with%20a%20fight%20for%20doctors%20to%20find%20the%20root%20cause.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOur%20son%2C%20Leo%2C%20was%20born%20healthy%20in%202015%2C%20but%20a%20childbirth%20injury%20disabled%20me%20for%20five%20years%20and%20nearly%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nytimes.com%2F2022%2F03%2F28%2Fwell%2Flive%2Fgaslighting-doctors-patients-health.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ecost%20me%20a%20leg%3C%2Fa%3E.%20The%20hits%20kept%20coming%20as%20steadily%20as%20Seattle's%20drizzling%20rain.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFive%20years%20stretched%20into%20eight%2C%20and%20I%20had%20long%20given%20up%20forming%20an%20attachment%20to%20our%20new%20city%20under%20the%20pressure%20of%20first-time%20parenthood%2C%20medical%20trauma%2C%20and%20Seattle's%20air%20of%20social%20isolation.%20Most%20days%2C%20I%20could%20barely%20get%20out%20of%20bed.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20was%20about%20this%20time%20when%20my%20husband%20and%20I%20began%20fantasizing%20about%20moving%20back%20to%20Chicago.%20The%20world%20was%20still%20in%20the%20throes%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcountries-on-lockdown-coronavirus-italy-2020-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ECOVID%20lockdown%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20but%20what%20if%20it%20weren't%3F%20Where%20would%20we%20be%20today%2C%20we%20wondered%2C%20if%20we%20still%20lived%20there%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWe%20romanticized%20Cubs%20games%2C%20the%20gritty%20%26quot%3BEl%26quot%3B%20train%2C%20and%20even%20our%20first%20apartment%20that%20blew%20a%20fuse%20every%20time%20we%20plugged%20in%20the%20toaster.%20Living%20in%20Chicago%20was%20objectively%20harder%2C%20but%20our%20lives%20were%20fuller%20back%20then.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWe%20weren't%20confined%20to%20hours%20spent%20in%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fus-cities-with-most-traffic-2019-2019-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Egridlock%20traffic%3C%2Fa%3E%20or%20constrained%20conversations%20that%20seemed%20to%20revolve%20around%20the%20same%20five%20topics%3A%20health%20problems%2C%20renovations%2C%20money%2C%20apathy%2C%20and%20%E2%80%94%20poignantly%20%E2%80%94%20when%20life%20would%20feel%20good%20again.%20We%20didn't%20sit%20at%20home%20in%20front%20of%20the%20TV%3B%20we%20were%20out%2C%20moving%2C%20doing%20new%20things.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOur%20son%20had%20never%20experienced%20that%20kind%20of%20freedom%2C%20and%20depriving%20him%20of%20it%20weighed%20on%20our%20minds.%20We%20were%20in%20%26quot%3B%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fquit-6-figure-jp-morgan-golden-handcuffs-job-money-2024-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Egolden%20handcuffs%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%26quot%3B%20chained%20by%20a%20lucrative%20job%20to%20a%20place%20we'd%20rather%20not%20be.%20We%20had%20bought%20into%20it%20in%20the%20beginning%2C%20not%20yet%20understanding%20that%20we%20were%20selling%20our%20quality%20of%20life.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%223034e216-f017-48a5-8cd7-9c7a4fd82bba%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EWe%20finally%20made%20the%20decision%20to%20leave%20in%20November%202023%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EI%20had%20just%20come%20home%20after%20another%20unplanned%20hospital%20stay.%20I%20looked%20around%20at%20the%20house%20we%20had%20remodeled%20together%3A%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmistakes-getting-floors-replaced-vinyl-plank-regrets-expensive-2024-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eshiny%20oak%20floors%3C%2Fa%3E%20laid%20in%20painstaking%20